description:
Infrared CO2 Sonsor Module (NDIR)
Range: 0~2000/5000/10000ppm (optional) 
Accuracy: +/- (50ppm +5% reading value)
Detection Gas: CO2
Working voltage 4.5 - 5.5V DC
Only Boards with multiple UART connections (e.g. Arduino MEGA) runn
name: mh-z19b

SybhlGG2P.content:
MH-Z19B CO2 Sensor from Winsen

https://www.winsen-sensor.com/d/files/infrared-gas-sensor/mh-z19b-co2-ver1_0.pdf

Funcitons:

CO2 Read
ON/OFF Self Calibration (False -> OFF, True -> ON)
Detection Range (False ->2000ppm, True -> 10000ppm)

N/A Functions: (function preparet in Node)
ZERO Point Calibration
SPAN Point Calibration

Testet with:
Only Controller with (UART1 till UART3) is running and debug
Arduino MEGA

BkUZwqbdbnP.content: ON/OFF Self-calibration function for zero point

SywvPwy2P.content:
Commands:
0x86 -> Read CO2 concentration
0x87 -> Calibrate Zero Point (ZERO)
0x88 -> Calibrate Span Point (SPAN)
0x79 -> ON/OFF Self-calibration function for zero point
0x99 -> Detection range setting

CO2 concentration = HIGH*256+LOW

B1oQV_W3w.description: Calibartion Enable for ZERO Point. If True Calibratoin is Active
B1oQV_W3w.label: C_Zero

H1leVdZ2P.description: Only after Zero Calibration. Span Point (SPAN) calibration is Enabled
H1leVdZ2P.label: SPAN

HyeQBuZ3D.description: Calibartion Enable for SPAN Point if True.
HyeQBuZ3D.label: C_Span

rJWBuxz3D.description: Bring sensor 20min in 2000ppm condition to calibrate
rJWBuxz3D.label: SPAN_C

rJxzEdW2w.description: ON/OFF Self-calibration function for zero point
rJxzEdW2w.label: S-Cal
